<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920106-0134</DOCNO><DOCID>920106-0134.</DOCID><HL>   Jamesway Sales Decline 3.8%</HL><DATE>01/06/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B5</SO><CO>   JMY</CO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)</MS><IN>BROADLINE RETAILERS, DEPARTMENT STORES (RTB)</IN><RE>NEW JERSEY (NJ)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   SECAUCUS, N.J. -- Discount retailer Jamesway Corp. saidsales for the four weeks ended Dec. 28 fell 3.8% to $120.9million, excluding leased departments.   Although same-store sales rose 4%, Herbert Fisher,chairman, said they were below plan. December sales were lesspromotional than a year ago, he added.</LP><TEXT>   Sales for the 47 weeks ended Dec. 28 fell 4.8% to $811.3million, while same-store sales rose 1%. Jamesway operated122 stores in seven states in December 1991, compared with136 stores a year ago.</TEXT></DOC>